############################################################################

For conversion tex files into pdf you have to run:

$ pdflatex <filename>

where <filename> is the name of tex file for which you want to generate pdf

############################################################################

System requirements:
	LaTeX installed to compile tex files into pdf
	OpenOffice.org Writer or Libreoffice Writer to edit or view odt
	Plain text editor to edit or view tex files
	PDF viewer to view pdf files

############################################################################

To edit or view tex files you need just plain-text editor

Terminal based text editors:
	vi, vim, nano etc.

Graphical user interface text editors:
	gedit, kwrite etc.

TeX editors:
	texmaker, kile etc.

